    "post_title": "Visiting the Scenes of Minneapolis Protests",
    "post_link": "https://www.billgeorge.org/articles/visiting-the-scenes-of-minneapolis-protests/",
    "post_date": "June 17, 2020",
    "post_content": [
      "<p>On Monday evening my men’s prayer group and I visited the heart of the Lake Street protests, led by member John Cuningham who lives in the neighborhood, one block from the protests. This is an extremely diverse neighborhood, very peaceful with no crime.</p><p>At the start of our tour we walked past the boarded-up buildings on Lake St. The sidewalks &amp; streets were cleaned, thanks to hundreds of people who came to clean up that first Saturday.</p><div><blockimg aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-8280\" class=\"wp-image-8280 \" src=\"https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3851-1-300x121.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"330\" height=\"133\" srcset=\"https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3851-1-300x121.jpeg 300w, https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3851-1-1024x413.jpeg 1024w, https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3851-1-768x310.jpeg 768w, https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3851-1-1536x620.jpeg 1536w, https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3851-1-2048x827.jpeg 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 330px) 100vw, 330px\"></blockimg><p id=\"caption-attachment-8280\" class=\"wp-caption-text\"><em>Boarded up buildings on Lake Street</em></p></div><blockimg aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-8280\" src=\"https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3851-1-300x121.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"330\" height=\"133\" srcset=\"https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3851-1-300x121.jpeg 300w, https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3851-1-1024x413.jpeg 1024w, https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3851-1-768x310.jpeg 768w, https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3851-1-1536x620.jpeg 1536w, https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3851-1-2048x827.jpeg 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 330px) 100vw, 330px\"></blockimg><p><em>Boarded up buildings on Lake Street</em></p><em>Boarded up buildings on Lake Street</em><p>Our 1<sup>st</sup> stop was at Urban Ventures food bank, co-located in the Jesuit school’s gym, which is providing free food &amp; supplies to local residents.</p><sup>st</sup><div><blockimg aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-8281\" class=\"wp-image-8281 size-medium\" src=\"https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3854-300x225.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" srcset=\"https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3854-300x225.jpeg 300w, https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3854-1024x768.jpeg 1024w, https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3854-768x576.jpeg 768w, https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3854-1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3854-rotated.jpeg 2016w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\"></blockimg><p id=\"caption-attachment-8281\" class=\"wp-caption-text\"><em>Inside of Urban Ventures</em></p></div><blockimg aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-8281\" src=\"https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3854-300x225.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" srcset=\"https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3854-300x225.jpeg 300w, https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3854-1024x768.jpeg 1024w, https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3854-768x576.jpeg 768w, https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3854-1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3854-rotated.jpeg 2016w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\"></blockimg><p><em>Inside of Urban Ventures</em></p><em>Inside of Urban Ventures</em><p>Here’s a great article on their work: <a href=\"http://strib.mn/2YIHaBT\">http://strib.mn/2YIHaBT</a>. Urban Ventures had previously created detailed catalog of 170 businesses in the immediate area. Since many were looted or damaged during the protests, Urban Ventures is raising funds to give them – no questions asked or forms to be filled out – to help them get back in business immediately with merchandise, repairs, etc.</p><a href=\"http://strib.mn/2YIHaBT\">http://strib.mn/2YIHaBT</a><p>We walked around the Auto Zone store set on fire by professional arsonists &amp; burned to the ground with temps &gt; 1500 degrees F., reducing it to a pile of rubble.</p><div><blockimg aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-8282\" class=\"wp-image-8282 size-medium\" src=\"https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3857-225x300.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3857-225x300.jpeg 225w, https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3857-768x1024.jpeg 768w, https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3857-1152x1536.jpeg 1152w, https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3857-rotated.jpeg 1512w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 225px) 100vw, 225px\"></blockimg><p id=\"caption-attachment-8282\" class=\"wp-caption-text\"><em>Auto Zone ruins</em></p></div><blockimg aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-8282\" src=\"https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3857-225x300.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3857-225x300.jpeg 225w, https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3857-768x1024.jpeg 768w, https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3857-1152x1536.jpeg 1152w, https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3857-rotated.jpeg 1512w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 225px) 100vw, 225px\"></blockimg><p><em>Auto Zone ruins</em></p><em>Auto Zone ruins</em><p>Next we saw the burned down post office – a favorite with local residents – with only its brick walls remaining.</p><div><blockimg aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-8283\" class=\"wp-image-8283 size-medium\" src=\"https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3858-300x225.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" srcset=\"https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3858-300x225.jpeg 300w, https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3858-rotated.jpeg 640w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\"></blockimg><p id=\"caption-attachment-8283\" class=\"wp-caption-text\"><em>Burned out post office</em></p></div><blockimg aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-8283\" src=\"https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3858-300x225.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" srcset=\"https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3858-300x225.jpeg 300w, https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3858-rotated.jpeg 640w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\"></blockimg><p><em>Burned out post office</em></p><em>Burned out post office</em><p>Then we passed by the new 5<sup>th</sup> precinct station, completely undamaged because local police previously established such good relationships with neighbors, who frequently use the station for community meetings.</p><sup>th</sup><div><blockimg aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-8284\" class=\"wp-image-8284 size-medium\" src=\"https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3859-300x225.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" srcset=\"https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3859-300x225.jpeg 300w, https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3859-rotated.jpeg 640w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\"></blockimg><p id=\"caption-attachment-8284\" class=\"wp-caption-text\"><em>5th precinct building</em></p></div><blockimg aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-8284\" src=\"https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3859-300x225.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" srcset=\"https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3859-300x225.jpeg 300w, https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3859-rotated.jpeg 640w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\"></blockimg><p><em>5th precinct building</em></p><em>5th precinct building</em><p>Finally, we came to the burned out Wells Fargo branch office.</p><div><blockimg aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-8285\" class=\"wp-image-8285 size-medium\" src=\"https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3861-300x225.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" srcset=\"https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3861-300x225.jpeg 300w, https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3861-rotated.jpeg 640w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\"></blockimg><p id=\"caption-attachment-8285\" class=\"wp-caption-text\"><em>Wells Fargo branch</em></p></div><blockimg aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-8285\" src=\"https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3861-300x225.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" srcset=\"https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3861-300x225.jpeg 300w, https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3861-rotated.jpeg 640w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\"></blockimg><p><em>Wells Fargo branch</em></p><em>Wells Fargo branch</em><p>Cuningham, one of the nation’s leading architects, lives in the renovated Victorian house built by his great-grandfather in 1898.</p><div><blockimg aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-8286\" class=\"wp-image-8286 size-medium\" src=\"https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3862-225x300.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3862-225x300.jpeg 225w, https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3862-768x1024.jpeg 768w, https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3862-1152x1536.jpeg 1152w, https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3862-rotated.jpeg 1512w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 225px) 100vw, 225px\"></blockimg><p id=\"caption-attachment-8286\" class=\"wp-caption-text\"><em>Architect John Cuningham in front of his home</em></p></div><blockimg aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-8286\" src=\"https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3862-225x300.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3862-225x300.jpeg 225w, https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3862-768x1024.jpeg 768w, https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3862-1152x1536.jpeg 1152w, https://www.billgeorge.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_3862-rotated.jpeg 1512w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 225px) 100vw, 225px\"></blockimg><p><em>Architect John Cuningham in front of his home</em></p><em>Architect John Cuningham in front of his home</em><p>He assured us the locals all protested peacefully until the arsonists arrived with 8 black SUVs with no license plates &amp; dropped incendiaries in trash cans as well as buildings.</p><p>It was a moving experience, tragic, yet hopeful due to attitudes of local residents and merchants to rebuild their community.</p><div></div>"
