nherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: black; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://www.sfgate.com/?controllerName=search&amp;action=search&amp;channel=business%2Fbloomberg&amp;search=1&amp;inlineLink=1&amp;query=%22Bob+Alexander%22\">Bob Alexander</a>,&nbsp;<a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: black; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://www.sfgate.com/?controllerName=search&amp;action=search&amp;channel=business%2Fbloomberg&amp;search=1&amp;inlineLink=1&amp;query=%22R.+Brad+Martin%22\">R. Brad Martin</a>, Frederic Poses and&nbsp;<a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: black; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://www.sfgate.com/?controllerName=search&amp;action=search&amp;channel=business%2Fbloomberg&amp;search=1&amp;inlineLink=1&amp;query=%22Vincent+Intrieri%22\">Vincent Intrieri</a>&nbsp;to its board, according to a statement today from the Oklahoma City-based company McClendon co-founded 23 years&nbsp;ago.</span></p><span>Chesapeake named&nbsp;<a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: black; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://www.sfgate.com/?controllerName=search&amp;action=search&amp;channel=business%2Fbloomberg&amp;search=1&amp;inlineLink=1&amp;query=%22Bob+Alexander%22\">Bob Alexander</a>,&nbsp;<a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: black; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://www.sfgate.com/?controllerName=search&amp;action=search&amp;channel=business%2Fbloomberg&amp;search=1&amp;inlineLink=1&amp;query=%22R.+Brad+Martin%22\">R. Brad Martin</a>, Frederic Poses and&nbsp;<a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baselin