    "post_title": "200 Minnesotans You Should Know",
    "post_link": "https://www.billgeorge.org/articles/200-minnesotans-you-should-know/",
    "post_date": "April 1, 2010",
    "post_content": [
      "<p><em>Originally Posted in the <a href=\"http://www.tcbmag.com/superstars/200minnesotansyoushouldknow/index.aspx\">Twin Cities Business Magazine</a> on April 1, 2010.<br></em></p><em>Originally Posted in the <a href=\"http://www.tcbmag.com/superstars/200minnesotansyoushouldknow/index.aspx\">Twin Cities Business Magazine</a> on April 1, 2010.<br></em><a href=\"http://www.tcbmag.com/superstars/200minnesotansyoushouldknow/index.aspx\">Twin Cities Business Magazine</a><br><p>There are people you simply should know.</p><p>They are people who shape your world, whether you recognize it or  not—people who come up in casual discussions, who frame points of view,  whose very names form points of reference.</p><p>On the following pages, you will find profiles of CEOs of Minnesota’s  largest companies, public and private. You will find lenders, venture  capitalists, and other financiers.</p><p>Even if you don’t know them personally, you should know who they are  and what they do—assuming, of course, that your world is the business  world, and that much of your business is done in Minnesota.</p><p>You will also see, on the pages that follow, entrepreneurs, including  individuals who have started several enterprises. There are builders—of  buildings and businesses—and thought leaders, public influencers, and  leaders of some of the not-for-profit enterprises that enrich your  world. Leaders of law and accounting firms also appear.</p><p>Who won’t you find? Prince, the musician—even though it would be  pitiable not to know his best productions. Twins catcher Joe Mauer, even  though your life will be improved by watching him work. You won’t find  Governor Tim Pawlenty, the novelist Vince Flynn, or the guy who played  Scrooge last year at the Guthrie Theater. We are presenting a roster of  people who occupy the business community. We left off professional  athletes, actors, entertainers, writers, artists, and all but a few  educators.</p><p>We also left out crooks—there’s no profile of Tom Petters—and elected  officials, although we hope we don’t have to remind you that you should  know the names of your representative in Congress, the mayor of the  city in which you live, and your state senator and representative. We  never considered including journalists.</p><p>Is 200 the right number of names? Well, sure it is. It highlights the fact that this is the 200th issue of <em>Twin Cities Business. </em></p><em>Twin Cities Business. </em><p>A better question is whether my associates and I—Gene Rebeck, Christa  Meland, Melissa Loth, Eric Kelsey—and a group of freelancers who  regularly contribute to the magazine have selected the right 200 people  to feature. And that’s where you come in.</p><p>As you know, part of the fun of reading a who’s who–style feature  like this is discovering names you might not have thought to include. As  we know—and please recognize that we do know this—there is also  frustration in finding that the people compiling the list have left off  someone who clearly, unequivocally should be on it.</p><p>So here’s what we’ll do: We’ll take your suggestions at  200plus@tcbmag.com. Send us the person’s name, title, company or  organization name, and no more than 150 words about why he or she is a  Minnesotan to know, and we’ll post your <span style=\"font-family: verdana,geneva;\">additions, too. &nbsp;</span>&nbsp;</p><span>additions, too. &nbsp;</span><p><strong>The 200 Minnesotans List</strong></p><strong>The 200 Minnesotans List</strong><p>1 <a href=\"http://www.tcbmag.com/superstars/superstars/127498p1.aspx\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Agin Schmidt, Carolyn</span></a> – Law Office of Carolyn Agin Schmidt</p><a href=\"http://www.tcbmag.com/superstars/superstars/127498p1.aspx\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Agin Schmidt, Carolyn</span></a><span>Agin Schmidt, Carolyn</span><p>2 <a href=\"http://www.tcbmag.com/superstars/superstars/127538p1.aspx\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Ames, Richard</span></a> – Ames Construction</p><a href=\"http://www.tcbmag.com/superstars/superstars/127538p1.aspx\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Ames, Richard</span></a><span>Ames, Richard</span><p>3 <a href=\"http://www.tcbmag.com/superstars/superstars/127391p1.aspx\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Amplatz, Kurt</span></a> – AGA Medical Holdings</p><a href=\"http://www.tcbmag.com/superstars/superstars/127391p1.aspx\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Amplatz, Kurt</span></a><span>Amplatz, Kurt</span><p>4 <a href=\"http://www.tcbmag.com/superstars/superstars/127392p1.aspx\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Anderson, Lee</span></a> – APi Group</p><a href=\"http://www.tcbmag.com/superstars/superstars/127392p1.aspx\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Anderson, Lee</span></a><span>Anderson, Lee</span><p>5 <a href=\"http://www.tcbmag.com/superstars/superstars/127577p1.aspx\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Annexstad, Al</span></a> – Federated Insurance Companies</p><a href=\"http://www.tcbmag.com/superstars/superstars/127577p1.aspx\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Annexstad, Al</span></a><span>Annexstad, Al</span><p>6 <a href=\"http://www.tcbmag.com/superstars/superstars/127393p1.aspx\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Austin, William</span></a> – Starkey Laboratories</p><a href=\"http://www.tcbmag.com/superstars/superstars/127393p1.aspx\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Austin, William</span></a><span>Austin, William</span><p>7 <a href=\"http://www.tcbmag.com/superstars/superstars/127394p1.aspx\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Avent, Sharon</span></a> – Smead Manufacturing Company</p><a href=\"http://www.tcbmag.com/superstars/superstars/127394p1.aspx\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Avent, Sharon</span></a><span>Avent, Sharon</span><p>8 <a href=\"http://www.tcbmag.com/superstars/superstars/127313p1.aspx\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Bachman, Dale</span></a> – Bachman’s</p><a href=\"http://www.tcbmag.com/superstars/superstars/127313p1.aspx\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Bachman, Dale</span></a><