    "post_date": "August 1, 2008",
    "post_content": [
      "<p align=\"left\">True North Selected for The Management Gurus: Lessons from the Best Management Books of All Time</p><p align=\"left\">True North: Discover Your Authentic Leadership, written by Bill George with Peter Sims in 2007, has been selected as one of fifteen books for The Management Gurus: Lessons from the Best Management Books of All Time. Edited by Chris Lauer and the editors at Soundview Executive Book Summaries and published by Portfolio, The Management Gurus features a 17-page summary and highlights of True North.</p><p>Among the other leading authors selected for The Management Gurus – and “the best management books of all time” – are the following:</p><ul>\n<li>Warren Bennis and Noel Tichy for Judgment (2007)</li>\n<li>Don Tapscott and Anthony Williams for Wikinomics (2006)</li>\n<li>Charles Handy for Gods of Management (1978)</li>\n<li>James Kouzes and Barry Posner for The Leadership Challenge (1987)</li>\n<li>Marshall Goldsmith for What Got You Here Won’t Get You There (2007)</li>\n<li>Jeffrey Krames for Jack Welch and the 4E’s of Leadership (2005)</li>\n<li>Kenichi Ohmae for The Next Global Stage (2005)</li>\n<li>Frances Hesselbein for The Leader of the Future (1996)</li>\n<li>John Maxwell for Winning with People (2004)</li>\n<li>Geoffrey Moore for Dealing with Darwin (2006)</li>\n</ul><li>Warren Bennis and Noel Tichy for Judgment (2007)</li><li>Don Tapscott and Anthony Williams for Wikinomics (2006)</li><li>Charles Handy for Gods of Management (1978)</li><li>James Kouzes and Barry Posner for The Leadership Challenge (1987)</li><li>Marshall Goldsmith for What Got You Here Won’t Get You There (2007)</li><li>Jeffrey Krames for Jack Welch and the 4E’s of Leadership (2005)</li><li>Kenichi Ohmae for The Next Global Stage (2005)</li><li>Frances Hesselbein for The Leader of the Future (1996)</li><li>John Maxwell for Winning with People (2004)</li><li>Geoffrey Moore for Dealing with Darwin (2006)</li>"
